rComments: Very poorly taught. An absolute mess - lectures had no direction, slides were barely used, and I did not feel adequately prepared for the midterm or exam, both of which asked too many questions for the two hours we were provided. Not recommended at all. Should probably stick to her research.

A very poorly taught course by a professor who assigned material that would benefit her career. She lost my essay, assigned acts of opera that did not exist and was not familiar with the operas studied. Dull and inefficient. Mandatory trip to an expensive opera, not listed in the course description. I would not take a course with her ever again.

I initially thought she was a really boring prof, but after taking a few other classes with her, you realize that she does examine things in depth, and you really have to look past what she is saying to completely understand- the fact that she works more of a guide to the material, and lets the students make the points and conclusions is art.

I guess if I took her Opera class, I'd like her more. And yeah. She's boring as hell. She doesn't add anything to the readings. But then the course itself is gonna be difficult to teach since it's new and shaky. Whatever. I never came to class, and if I did I slept. BUT, go to the lecture that Trish Lamie is guest-professoring at. I missed it :(

SHE'S CRAZY! I love art and am very interested in it but she managed to ruin it for me so bad that I never took any course in that discpline again. You will hate her and the way she teaches the course because she'll drive you NUTS. She's very narrow-minded and does not know how to work any of the equipment in her class. Generally, NOT RECOMMANDED!
it was so boring it wasn't even funny.  the readings couldn't even hold my attention for more then 2 minutes.  and lectures... just boring... overall a dud course...

She is deluded, I think she found her muse while smoking a crack pipe out back…Horrible communication skills & her teaching style is bias only focusing on music & completely ignoring the other art sectors.. u know it’s bad when people were ordering pizza in class, throwing apples and other unmentionables at her, god UTSC, we are all so brilliant!
Unlike most of my profs, I really like her. She seems pretty easy and I really enjoy her lectures.
IF U WANNA PASS THIS CLASS...JUST PRINT ALL HER LECTURE NOTES AND READ THE READERS DO GOOD AT TUT...U DO NOT EVEN HAVE TO SHOW UP AT HER BORING LECTURES
The reading material was interesting, but Clark has no control over her class. She's also a bit of a snoozer. I stopped going to lectures after the mid-term and came out with an A-.
I loved this class and its content. Tutorials are more helpful than anything. I probably would have never known about the Music Garden without this class!
probally the worst professor that i have ever had. She does not know how to teach.  she also has a wierd obsession with YO YO MA

She knows a lot about music and only music and doesn't seem to touch upon other arts (Drama, Studio, Art History).  She can be really boring and even though she CAN be nice, I think it's just an act.. =(

Collaborations has become the bane of all Arts majors at UTSC.  Clark spends the majority of the lectures trying to work the A/V equipment and puts many people to sleep.  I stopped going to the lectures and just went to the tutorials and still got a C+

Summarizes & clarifies text every class.  If you go to her lectures, just skim through the readings before class -- no need to deep read.  Takes notes during her lectures instead.  Using an English dictionary is strongly recommended for =everyone=.
